‘’Ů@cfc93c96a76f9b1010f99219d9edb955b4da3bb221a9be38064bd882c06ee417ÚzTitle: This week in Nu #14
Path: This week in Nu #14
Content:
Released 0.6.0!
thegedge refactored how commands are classified as part of a pipeline refactor (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1008] #1008
)
andrasio extended 
``nth``
 to allow more than one row number (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1011] #1011
), added 
``default``
 (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1006] #1006
) and 
``compact``
 (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1003] #1003
)
est31 upgraded us to the latest Cargo.toml format (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1026] #1026
)
bndbsh added 
``=~``
 and 
``!~``
 for fuzzy string comparisons (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/997] #997
)
jonathandturner added expansion of ~ in externals (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1014] #1014
) and fixed some printing issues (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1017] #1017
),
wycats began a multi-part refactoring to get our source code ready for the next set of features (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1009] #1009
)
sebastian-xyz and Aloso worked to get the websites easier to read and more consistent across platforms, including mobile
sebastian-xyz also helped document more commands (you can see all the hard work on command documentation starting to pay off on the new website in the Docs section!)
